SIMPLE: tilth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tilth
<hw>Tilth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>til<?/</ets>,
fr. <ets>tilian</ets> to till. See <er>Till</er> to cultivate.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being tilled, or prepared for a crop;
culture; <as>as, land is good <ex>tilth</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>tilth</qex> and rank fertility of its golden youth.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is tilled; tillage ground.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And so by <qex>tilth</qex> and grange . . . ⟦br⟧
We gained the mother city.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tilt hammer</ent>⟦br⟧
